# Service Layer

## Service Class Structure
```java
@Log4j2
@Service
public class OrderService {
    private final OrderDal orderDal;
    private final EventPublisher eventPublisher;
    private final OrderMapper mapper;

    public OrderService(OrderDal dal, EventPublisher publisher, OrderMapper mapper) {
        this.orderDal = dal;
        this.eventPublisher = publisher;
        this.mapper = mapper;
    }
}
```

## SPI (Extension Point) Pattern
```java
public interface NotificationBuilder {
    Notification build(EventData data);
}

@Component
@ConditionalOnMissingBean(NotificationBuilder.class)
public class DefaultNotificationBuilder implements NotificationBuilder {
    // Default used when no extension is provided
}
```
Downstream modules override defaults by providing their own `@Component` implementation.

## Conventions
- Constructor injection — **no field injection**
- Inject DALs (not repositories directly) for persistence
- Use MapStruct mappers for object transformation
- `@ConditionalOnMissingBean` for default SPI implementations
- `application.yaml` for configuration (not `.properties`)
